title: Deceptive Visualization
description: Designed a subtly deceptive data visualization to purposely mislead the viewer. Learned how design elements and visual encodings can be used to convey both accurate and inaccurate information.

title: Expository Visualization
description: Designed an expository visualization to clearly communicate an idea based on a small data set. My visualization answers questions about sunshine fluctuation between major U.S. cities throughout the year.

title: Power Outage Analysis
description: Investigated the question: Which characteristics are associated with power outages in different regions of the U.S.? Created a model to predict the severity of a power outage based on certain data features.

title: Image Classifier
description: Created a program to identify image features and classify an inputted image based on the time of day using a KNN algorithm. Thoroughly tested program in different scenarios to ensure optimal functionality.

title: Spell Checker
description: Implemented spell checker functionality using Java. When the spell checker comes across a misspelled word, it gives suggestions for correctly spelled words that are similar to the misspelled word that the user typed.

title: Priority Queue Implementation
description: Produced a working priority queue using dHeap (heap with d branching factor). Programmed methods to insert elements, remove elements, retrieve elements, check if empty, and clear the queue.

title: Sorting Algorithm Runtime Analysis
description: Analyzed the runtimes of different sorting algorithms such as insertion sort, quick sort, count sort, etc. Tested the scalability of sorting algorithms and created plots to communicate the results.

title: DNA To Protein Transformer
description: Created a program to transform a sequence of DNA into RNA, and then transform that RNA into proteins. Made use of circular queues to store information.

title: Spotify Artist Discography Analysis
description: Developed a song recommender tool that takes an inputted song and finds the most similar song, based on the euclidean distance between audio features. Utilized TF-IDF to determine the lyric that best summarizes a song.

title: Meteorite Probability Analysis
description: Conducted hypothesis and permutation tests to analyze distributions of meteorite data, applying statistical methods and drawing meaningful insights. Visualized results using Matplotlib and Plotly.
